	</article><!-- #post -->
							
	<article id="post-3487" class="post-3487 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-poetry category-politics">
				<header class="entry-header">
			
						<h1 class="entry-title">
				<a href="https://joshhansen.net/2017/01/fired/" rel="bookmark">Fired</a>
			</h1>
										<div class="comments-link">
					<a href="https://joshhansen.net/2017/01/fired/#comments">1 Reply</a>				</div><!-- .comments-link -->
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<div style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img width="1024" height="683" alt="" src="https://joshhansen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/wp-1485852299276.jpg" title="A little ember" class="size-full wp-image-3486" srcset="https://joshhansen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/wp-1485852299276.jpg 1024w, https://joshhansen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/wp-1485852299276-430x287.jpg 430w, https://joshhansen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/wp-1485852299276-768x512.jpg 768w, https://joshhansen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/wp-1485852299276-624x416.jpg 624w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Photo: John Murphy. CC-BY-SA 2.0.</p></div>
<p>It&#8217;s like a fire.<br />
It burns,<br />
The anxiety, the fierce desire<br />
To preserve this reserve<br />
Of liberty<br />
To maintain the promise<br />
The magic<br />
The myth<br />
Of us as one people<br />
Of government for us<br />
And by us<br />
And of us.<br />
Oh let it not perish<br />
From the earth.<br />
Let not our times<br />
Be the times<br />
When all that blood<br />
In all that dirt<br />
Cries out our failure against us.<br />
Let not our days<br />
Be the days<br />
When the golden age fades<br />
And the light that they left us<br />
Casts its last ray.<br />
No, let it not<br />
Be in our days.</p>
<p><i>That</i> is the fire.<br />
<i>That</i>&nbsp;the desire.<br />
Let the flame burn higher.<br />
Higher and higher<br />
Even be it now<br />
But a tiny spark.<br />
That&#8217;s all it takes.<br />
That&#8217;s how it starts.</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
